         <div type="translation" xml:lang="eng" resp="part:emfr">
			<p>Prosperity! Fortune!</p>
			<p>Third year of the victorious king Nandivarman (kō-vicaiya-nantivikkiramaparumaṉ).</p>
			<p>Aṭavi, the lord (kiḻavaṉ) of Tiruppālaiyūr in Perumpālaiyūr in the district (kōṭṭam) of Ūṟṟukkāṭu, after having made request to the glorious king of the Gaṅgas, the mukhamaṇḍapa that Aṭavi made for his own mother Naṅkaṉi Naṅkaiyār.</p>
			<p>This, the feet of he who protects it without destroying it are on my head.</p>
			</div>
			
